[{"short_id":"x4xkq8","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/x4xkq8","created_at":"2024-07-18T07:44:36.000-05:00","title":"Good news - streamlined authorization management now generally available","url":"","score":-4,"flags":5,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eCerbos Hub is now generally available. If you’re looking for a powerful authorization solution, this might be just what you need.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAuthorization logic can become complex and hard to manage. Writing and maintaining this code within the application leads to bloat, complicates development, and increases the risk of errors. Cerbos Hub helps externalize and manage this logic efficiently.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere are some key benefits of the solution, that I believe it’d be relevant to share:\nEliminates Code Bloat: Centralize your authorization policies to avoid duplicative and scattered code within your applications.\nSimplifies Policy Management: Manage policies centrally with an intuitive interface, reducing the burden on your development team.\nEnables Collaborative Policy Authoring: Build and test policies collaboratively using a web IDE with YAML templates.\nIncludes Seamless CI/CD Integration: Test and deploy policies across development, testing, and production environments effortlessly.\nEmpowers Versatile Deployment: Supports on-premise, cloud, serverless, and edge environments, ensuring your policies are in sync everywhere.\nIncludes Embedded PDP: Perform authorization checks directly from end-user devices using WebAssembly modules, reducing latency and enhancing security.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo, in case anyone is looking to solve their authorization headache, do check out Cerbos Hub.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Cerbos Hub is now generally available. If you’re looking for a powerful authorization solution, this might be just what you need.\r\n\r\nAuthorization logic can become complex and hard to manage. Writing and maintaining this code within the application leads to bloat, complicates development, and increases the risk of errors. Cerbos Hub helps externalize and manage this logic efficiently.\r\n\r\nHere are some key benefits of the solution, that I believe it’d be relevant to share:\r\nEliminates Code Bloat: Centralize your authorization policies to avoid duplicative and scattered code within your applications.\r\nSimplifies Policy Management: Manage policies centrally with an intuitive interface, reducing the burden on your development team.\r\nEnables Collaborative Policy Authoring: Build and test policies collaboratively using a web IDE with YAML templates.\r\nIncludes Seamless CI/CD Integration: Test and deploy policies across development, testing, and production environments effortlessly.\r\nEmpowers Versatile Deployment: Supports on-premise, cloud, serverless, and edge environments, ensuring your policies are in sync everywhere.\r\nIncludes Embedded PDP: Perform authorization checks directly from end-user devices using WebAssembly modules, reducing latency and enhancing security.\r\n\r\nSo, in case anyone is looking to solve their authorization headache, do check out Cerbos Hub.","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/x4xkq8/good_news_streamlined_authorization","submitter_user":"AnnaP","user_is_author":true,"tags":["practices","scaling","security","testing","web"]},{"short_id":"stkaeo","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/stkaeo","created_at":"2024-07-18T07:34:41.000-05:00","title":"Slint 1.7 Released with New Widgets, Multi-Window Support, and Live-Preview Redesign","url":"https://slint.dev/blog/slint-1.7-released","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/stkaeo/slint_1_7_released_with_new_widgets_multi","submitter_user":"hunger","user_is_author":false,"tags":["c++","javascript","python","rust"]},{"short_id":"mmokay","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/mmokay","created_at":"2024-07-18T06:10:31.000-05:00","title":"Pixi - repro